# Initial Dependency Installation

Use these commands when setting up application. Prefer `npm` so the lockfile and installs stay consistent across contributors.

## 1) Create app shell (new project only)

```bash
npx create-next-app@latest project-name
```
- Use previously used setting which are 'TypeScript, ESLint, No React Compiler, Tailwind CSS, src/ directory, App Router'

## 2) Install runtime dependencies

```bash
npm install @prisma/client @prisma/adapter-pg bcryptjs dotenv jose pg react-icons react-responsive zod
```

## 3) Install development dependencies

```bash
npm install --save-dev prisma tsx @types/pg
```

## 4) Initialize and wire Prisma

```bash
npx prisma init --db --output @/app/generated/prisma
```
- Install latest version (v7^)
- Say yes to authentication redirecting user to prisma site for login and db setup
- Project name should be the same as root directory folder name

After env values are set (`DATABASE_URL`, `SESSION_SECRET`), run:


## 5) Final setup additions

- Add `SESSION_SECRET` to `.env` file. To get a value for the key run `openssl rand -base64 32` or use another recommended method.
- Add `seed: 'tsx prisma/seed.ts'` to `migrations` object in `prisma.config.ts` file

## 6) Daily scripts

```bash
npm run dev      # local development
npm run lint     # code quality checks
npm run build    # production build
npm run start    # run built app
```

